## Complete the following using the `database` object
<pre class="code javascript" >
var database = {
  connect: function() { ... },
  disconnect: function() { ... },
  log: function() { ... },
  read: function() { ... }
};
</pre>

* _call_ **read** to get the next database record
* the **read** method will occasionally throw exceptions
* _write_ all exception messages to **log**
* `database` must call **connect** before you can read a record
* `database` must call **disconnect** before calling **connect** again
* only *one record* can be read *per open connection*

_( yes, this is the world's worst database... )_

[zone name:script.js for:try_catch syntax:javascript]
function load( database ) {

  // connect, read, and disconnect
  // log all errors

}


